radiographic_examinations.findings: Slightly larger collo-diaphyseal angles of the femur in both hip joints.
Patchy and slightly longer T2 signals in the white matter of both parietal lobes and slightly increased extra-cerebral space in both frontotemporal regions.
Normal with a patent foramen ovale at birth that was closed at 6 months of age.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The patent foramen ovale closed at 6 months of age.
